synthetic_edge_return_projection_oracle_gate.v1
================================================

Status: implemented, fresh evidence evaluated, metric failed.

Purpose
-------

This benchmark gate asks whether the forecast stack recovers the tradable
synthetic edge-return signal, not only raw node-feature signs.

The v1 projection is:

```text
quote node index: 0
quote node id:    SYNUSD
base node ids:    SYNALPHA,SYNBETA,SYNGAMMA
close feature:    target feature index 3
predicted edge:   expected_close(base) - expected_close(quote)
realized edge:    realized_close(base) - realized_close(quote)
```

Implemented Evidence Path
-------------------------

Fresh channel-MDN train/eval reports now emit:

```text
edge_return_projection_schema
edge_return_projection_quote_node_index
edge_return_projection_quote_node_id
edge_return_projection_base_node_ids
edge_return_projection_close_feature_index
edge_return_projection_valid_count
edge_return_projection_ev_mae
edge_return_projection_ev_rmse
edge_return_projection_signed_error
edge_return_projection_directional_accuracy
edge_return_projection_correlation
edge_return_projection_pairwise_rank_valid_count
edge_return_projection_pairwise_rank_accuracy
edge_return_projection_best_asset_valid_count
edge_return_projection_best_asset_agreement
edge_return_projection_valid_count_per_edge
edge_return_projection_directional_accuracy_per_edge
edge_return_projection_valid_count_per_channel
edge_return_projection_directional_accuracy_per_channel
```

Runtime copies these fields into `runtime.result.fact`, and Lattice carries
them in `lattice.forecast_eval.fact`.

Lattice Target
--------------

```text
TARGET_ID = synthetic_edge_return_projection_oracle_ready
TARGET_CLASS = synthetic_edge_return_projection_oracle_gate
SUBJECT_FACT_FAMILY = forecast_eval
PROOF_KIND = synthetic_edge_return_projection_oracle_bound
UPSTREAM_TARGET_ID = channel_mdn_certified_replay_expansion_eval_ready
OVER_SPLIT = certified_replay_expansion_eval
MAX_ORACLE_EDGE_RETURN_EV_MAE = 0.05
MAX_ORACLE_EDGE_RETURN_EV_RMSE = 0.075
MIN_ORACLE_EDGE_RETURN_DIRECTIONAL_ACCURACY = 0.95
MIN_ORACLE_EDGE_RETURN_PAIRWISE_RANK_ACCURACY = 0.95
MIN_ORACLE_EDGE_RETURN_BEST_ASSET_AGREEMENT = 0.60
MIN_ORACLE_EDGE_RETURN_CORRELATION = 0.25
WAVE_MODE = none
PLAN_MAX_ATTEMPTS = 0
```

Current Durable Evidence Result
-------------------------------

The rebuilt Runtime executor emitted fresh projection evidence, and the rebuilt
Lattice binary evaluated the new target against that evidence:

```text
target_id = synthetic_edge_return_projection_oracle_ready
status = metric_failed
proof_certificate_check_passed = true
deficit = metric:synthetic_edge_return_projection_oracle
certificate_ref = cert_37de59706418
certificate_digest = 37de597064185a9c
```

Fresh source evidence:

```text
job_id = cwu_02v_certified_replay_eval_mdn.run.channel_inference_mdn.attempt_000005
anchor_range = [760,1088)
lattice_forecast_eval_fact_digest = 5bbbd212b8c78549
runtime_result_fact_digest = 211edfdfed13acf4
forecast_eval_target_fact_digest = 8bbf94c81514c45b
projection_valid_count = 2952
projection_valid_count_per_edge = 984,984,984
projection_valid_count_per_channel = 984,984,984
```

The edge magnitude errors are finite and inside the current loose thresholds:

```text
edge_return_projection_ev_mae = 0.0219482   <= 0.05
edge_return_projection_ev_rmse = 0.0277461  <= 0.075
edge_return_projection_signed_error = -0.0003166
```

The tradable edge direction/ranking quality is near random and fails the oracle
thresholds:

```text
edge_return_projection_directional_accuracy = 0.507453 < 0.95
edge_return_projection_pairwise_rank_accuracy = 0.491531 < 0.95
edge_return_projection_best_asset_agreement = 0.295732 < 0.60
edge_return_projection_correlation = 0.00355936 < 0.25
edge_return_projection_directional_accuracy_per_edge = 0.465447,0.510163,0.546748
edge_return_projection_directional_accuracy_per_channel = 0.494919,0.515244,0.512195
```

Interpretation: the missing-evidence blocker is closed. The current
representation/MDN stack can emit projection evidence, and Lattice can score it,
but the projected tradable edge signal is effectively not learned on the
protected eval range.

Validation Performed
--------------------

```text
make -C src/main/hero build-lattice-hero -j12
make -C src/main/hero build-marshal-hero -j12
make -C src/main/hero build-runtime-hero -j12
make -C src/main/exec build-cuwacunu-exec -j12
temporarily set synthetic_benchmark.config runtime_wave_id=cwu_02v_certified_replay_eval_mdn
hero.runtime.run mode=dry_run selected cwu_02v_certified_replay_eval_mdn
hero.runtime.run mode=execute with checkpoint handoff produced attempt_000005
hero.lattice.evaluate.deficit target_id=synthetic_edge_return_projection_oracle_ready
restored synthetic_benchmark.config runtime_wave_id=policy_training_ppo_v0
hero.lattice.evaluate.deficit rechecked the same metric failure after config restore
```

Next Step
---------

Investigate why the representation/MDN stack has low edge-return direction and
rank recovery on a deterministic periodic benchmark. This should happen before
interpreting PPO policy performance as the primary failure, because the forecast
path now fails in tradable edge space before policy optimization.
